eenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   When can we start going to LGuk?</span><hr size=1> just want to know when it is good to start going. I am level 30 now, and have been trying to use the  quick experience tactics menetioned on this board. I don't know if it is because I am level 30, but it seems to be going excruciatingly slow, and i don't have the patience to sit on an island killing the same three dwarves over and over! Got about half a bub there in 2 hours, might as well go back to grouping.<br>
<br>
For regular groups i usually see two options. Cazic Thule or Highkeep. highkeep exp is very slow because not many people pul raiders, they just wait for the warrior room to pop, which gets boring. Cazic Thule is usually pressed for space, and hard to find a group. Another option is lower guk, but i don't know if I am high enough for the bedroom. I see 29ish clerics and enchanters go, but to be safe i was going to shoot for my 34 spells and pets before jumping into that. Should I hold off on LGuk, or would I actualy have a chance of surviving there? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Silverblade</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 1:55:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   head to the Frotnier Mountains</span><hr size=1> superb xp and mages can solo there from 34+ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Lunasicc</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 2:08:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Sister Island</span><hr size=1> I was actually 30 when I went to OOT for my focus quests.<br>
I was hunting at sister island while I /auc'd for gornit's toes.<br>
I would kill the 2 dwarfs, then run to the otherside and kill the 2 woodelfs who where not in cabins.<br>
<br>
When I was doing this at lvl 30 I was amazed at the exp I got over a few hours.<br>
I still find the best experiene at that level is when you have paw in SK all too yourself.<br>
<br>
p.s. Use a partner when needed, it makes it eazery to avoid your pet taking half the experience. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Kalamos</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 5:20:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Lower Guk</span><hr size=1> I just started going to Lower Guk a few levels ago.  I started in the Bedroom/Spider Room when I was around the middle of lvl 33.  The experience in that area is VERY good there and the loot is average.  You can be effective at 32-33 and even more so when you hit 34 when you get your new pets and more importantly new DDs (heh .. get ready for a few fizzles at first .. I hadn't used my Evocation skill for 10 levels <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  <br>
<br>
The risk of death in the Bedroom (Spider Room is better to pull the area to IMHO) with a full group is very low and the experience will fly.  The only dangers really are not being able to handle the Greater Icebones, a bad pull on the Icebones and they pass by the Ghoul Wizard ledge to pick up a few friends (quick death there), or your group gets trained (happens alot in Lower Guk).  But that's what gate is for right?  Know when to gate (usually when thwe main tank says RUN!) and know when to fight it out.<br>
<br>
I hit 36 a couple days ago and have been getting into groups in the Assasin/Supplier room.  Guk can be dangerous but it's great exp and great fun.  Get a good group down there and you're set.<br>
<br>
Kalamos Darksummons<br>
Magician of 36 Fizzles<br>
The 7th Hammer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Kalamos</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 5:35:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   I forgot something</span><hr size=1> Oh by the way .. I went from 30 to 33 very quickly soloing Golra in Tim Deep.  Not as fun as grouping but awesome exp and very safe.  Go there if you have Kunark.  You wont regret it.<br>
<br>
Kalamos Darksummons<br>
Magician of 36 Fizzles<br>
The 7th Hammer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usimmulcrum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Simm Ulcrum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 6:29:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   When can we start going to LGuk</span><hr size=1> I started going to Lguk at 35 in the assassin room.  One underrated place for lvl 25 to 33 is Sol A.  I found it better than Cazic.  Same loot with a vendor in zone.  The big problem is that not many people go there so you pretty much have to take a party with you to be able to go there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uascii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ascii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(11/17/00 5:45:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~crodley/Ascii/wave.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: When can we start going to LGuk</span><hr size=1> I REALLY agree with Kalamos,  The Golra's in Timerous Deep tookme from level 30 to level 39 in two weeks, of about 4-5 hoursper day.  Yes, it was boring, but the fast, fast exp kept meawake <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODEEMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Hop on the boat that goes to FV fromBB and when it leaves FV and zones back into Timerous Deep, hopoff (use that waterstone, cast a pet, in case) and swim to theiceberg at -9000 and -6000  Really, cast a pet before you startswimming because sometimes just getting up on the iceberg willagro the first golra inside the shipwreck.<br>
<br>
  Keep yourpet buffed, blast away and sit and med.  I had a spot where therewere 4 golras around me in a semi circle, I'd kill each one inorder, and only had to wait for full mana, never had all 4 spotsempty.<br>
<br>
Never saw a roaming mob, and only one personin all that time.<br>
<br>
At level 38 the golras were half green,but most of them STILL gave good exp, and I easily went to 39doing 50-50 greens blues, believe it or not.<br>
<br>
Like Isaid, if you have a TV next to your computer, watch a footballgame or movie and every 5 minutes stand and blast, you'll levelin no time.<br>
<br>
Oh ya, loot is anywhere from 4 copper (sillyVerant) to 5 plat and mostly Words and icecubes that sell foronly a gold or so each.  Oh yes, I DID get about 5-6 researchcomponents like Gloves of Rallos Zek and Flame of Vox, but 5-6 in 9 levels isn't great <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><imgsrc=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Ansi Toshiningsea<br>
Level 39 Magician<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufactioner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Factioner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(12/22/00 8:26:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eq.castersrealm.com/images/Magician_bg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: When can we start going to LGuk</span><hr size=1> 34 is when you can goto L Guk. Make sure you don't kill the live side. I don't know how many times I've seen people get the butts kicked and trained out by the dead only to be attacked again by the live side once the zone. I did alot of soloing here in L Guk. The best place is to sit in the first hallway to the left as you zone in. There are like 4 spawns here. 2 in the hall way and 2 on a ledge across the rinver. You can sit in the hallway and kill them as soon as they spawn. Good exp and good loot. If a tain comes through you are A. Close to the zone or B. Just run over the hill to the live side.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showPrevMessage?topicID=103.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showNextMessage?topicID=103.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ez